Indeed,

I wrote:

"I have seen about 4 totally unique adapters for Federal buses." 

What I should have said is, "I have seen about 4 totally unique adapters for
Federal buses with differently spaced holes, none which fit a US spec
plate."

Looks like your new lid falls into one of those categories and may not be
from a California model. Or it may be from a Canadian or European model.
Curiously, did the either lid have a yellow emissions sticker? I would love
to add this to my emissions trivia.

These buses are very mysterious...

It is unfortunate that you drilled the holes, I have a couple of the wider
adapters sitting in my parts bin. Your later more specific description made
me take a second look.

Oh, and I love your plate!

Jon Stiles

